
[1]amaze

   AMA'ZE, v.t.

   To confound with fear, sudden surprise, or wonder; to astonish.

   They shall be afraid; they shall be amazed at one another. Is. 23.

   They were all amazed and glorified God. Mark 2. Luke 5.

   This word implies astonishment or perplexity, arising from something
   extraordinary, unexpected,unaccountable, or frightful.

     AMA'ZE, n. Astonishment; confusion; perplexity, arising from fear,
       surprise or wonder. It is chiefly used in poetry, and is nearly
                         synonymous with amazement.
